Package: cleanTMLE
Title: Software Layer for an Outcome-Blind Staged Targeted-Learning Workflow
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: c(
    person("Andrew", "Mertens", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "amertens@berkeley.edu"),
    person("cleanTMLE Contributors", role = "ctb"))
Description: Software layer for an outcome-blind staged workflow for
    targeted-learning observational causal analyses. The package operates
    inside the broader clean-room governance construct of Muntner et al.
    (2024) by recording prespecification, design diagnostics, plasmode
    candidate selection, data-quality stress testing, and GO/FLAG/STOP
    checkpoint decisions before the observed primary treatment-outcome
    association is read. The v0.1 release is tested on binary point
    exposure with binary outcome and the marginal risk-difference
    estimand; outcome missingness is handled through complete-case and
    inverse-probability-of-censoring-weighting sensitivity paths under
    prespecified missingness assumptions. Supports three workflow
    families for the binary-outcome scope: conventional propensity-score
    methods (matching and inverse-probability-of-treatment weighting),
    fixed-specification targeted minimum loss-based estimation (TMLE),
    and simulation-selected TMLE in which candidate nuisance strategies
    are evaluated on plasmode simulations before real-outcome access.
    The plasmode loop is extended with a data-quality stress test
    ('run_plasmode_dq_stress') that evaluates each prespecified TMLE
    candidate under controlled covariate-missingness, treatment-
    misclassification, outcome-misclassification, and unmeasured-
    confounding scenarios, producing a degradation gradient that the
    GO/FLAG/STOP rule consumes on the same scale as the baseline
    plasmode metrics. Time-to-event helpers (IPW risk curves,
    g-computation, augmented IPW, IPW hazard ratios, survival TMLE
    via 'survtmle', and longitudinal TMLE via 'lmtp') are provided
    as experimental extensions and are not part of the v0.1 tested
    scope. SuperLearner ensemble learning is the default propensity-
    score estimation strategy. cleanTMLE provides a cohort-specification
    interface ('specify_models', 'identify_*'), reporting helpers
    ('make_table1', 'make_table2', 'extreme_weights',
    'inspect_ipw_weights', 'forest_plot'), the analysis lock, outcome
    masking, plasmode feasibility and DQ stress, audit and decision
    logs, the modular TMLE primitives, and the staged pre-outcome
    decision rule.
